During the third week of the Investing in America Tour, the Biden-Harris Administration announced significant investments in communities across the country. Vice President Kamala Harris announced $300 million in grant funding to improve nine bridges in communities from Columbia, SC to Detroit, MI, Madison, WI to San Diego, CA. The administration also announced investments to expand access to high-speed internet, advance environmental justice, and build a clean energy economy. The tour included over 50 events across nearly 30 states and territories, highlighting the impact of President Biden's policies on manufacturing, clean energy investments, small business growth, infrastructure, and communities. Various states, including California, Georgia, Kansas, Michigan, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, South Carolina, Virginia, and Wisconsin, received funding for various projects, such as bridge repairs, broadband expansion, housing, and environmental initiatives.